WEBVTT

00:02.368 --> 00:04.619
♪ My name is Cleveland Brown

00:04.621 --> 00:06.888
♪ And I am proud to be

00:06.890 --> 00:09.058
♪ Right back
In my hometown ♪

00:09.060 --> 00:11.660
♪ With my new family

00:11.662 --> 00:13.846
♪ There's old friends
And new friends ♪

00:13.848 --> 00:16.248
♪ And even a bear

00:16.250 --> 00:18.450
♪ Through good times
And bad times ♪

00:18.452 --> 00:20.051
♪ It's true love we share ♪

00:20.053 --> 00:22.187
♪ And so I found a place

00:22.189 --> 00:24.490
♪ Where everyone will know

00:24.492 --> 00:26.792
♪ My happy mustache face

00:26.794 --> 00:28.827
♪ This is <i>The Cleveland Show</i> ♪

00:28.829 --> 00:30.996
[LAUGHS]

00:30.998 --> 00:33.198
[♪]

00:36.019 --> 00:37.553
Love the pool,
Cleveland.

00:37.555 --> 00:39.287
Yeah,
who says pools need to--?

00:39.289 --> 00:41.823
Need to be in the ground
or look nice?

00:41.825 --> 00:43.108
I went into the Tar-zhay

00:43.110 --> 00:44.943
to get some medicated
arch supports

00:44.945 --> 00:48.013
and I walked out
with this sweet-ass pool.

00:48.015 --> 00:50.032
You walked out
with this whole pool?

00:50.034 --> 00:51.666
Fit in my trunk.

00:51.668 --> 00:53.668
Water not included.

00:53.670 --> 00:55.337
[PANTING]

00:55.339 --> 00:56.972
Nine rings. New record.

00:56.974 --> 01:00.476
Opened my eyes too.
No goggles. No regrets.

01:00.478 --> 01:02.160
You getting in, Junior?

01:02.162 --> 01:04.262
No. I don't like
to take my shirt off

01:04.264 --> 01:06.932
in front of people
on account of my Frisbee nips.

01:06.934 --> 01:11.770
Mine has grown together so they
look like the MasterCard logo.

01:11.772 --> 01:14.039
Heh-heh.
Priceless.

01:14.041 --> 01:15.474
[BOTH SIGH]

01:21.181 --> 01:23.031
[♪]

01:37.746 --> 01:39.747
[YELLS]

01:39.749 --> 01:42.334
Roberta, I don't mean
to embarrass you

01:42.336 --> 01:43.736
or sound old-fashioned

01:43.738 --> 01:46.238
but ye maidenhood showeth.

01:46.240 --> 01:47.907
My what?
Your...

01:47.909 --> 01:50.843
You know what? It doesn't
matter. You're doomed.

01:50.845 --> 01:52.745
Ow! Bitch!
My bad.

01:52.747 --> 01:53.879
From where I was standing,

01:53.881 --> 01:56.549
it looked like I was
throwing to a man.

01:56.551 --> 01:58.733
Rallo,
what did I tell you

01:58.735 --> 02:00.602
about getting too close
to this pool?

02:00.604 --> 02:03.689
Calm down, Donna. The boy's
just trying to have some fun.

02:03.691 --> 02:05.491
Don't tell me
to calm down.

02:05.493 --> 02:08.126
I told you I think this pool
is dangerous.

02:08.128 --> 02:10.996
It's like now we've got
two loaded guns in the house.

02:10.998 --> 02:13.131
Hey,
is that Djimon Hounsou?

02:13.133 --> 02:14.232
Where?

02:14.234 --> 02:15.734
[SCREAMS]

02:15.736 --> 02:18.737
Ha, ha. Now you gotta change
your clothes.

02:18.739 --> 02:21.407
And get your hair done.

02:21.409 --> 02:24.109
And get a new cell phone.

02:24.111 --> 02:26.345
[JUNIOR SNORING]

02:28.932 --> 02:32.134
Junior's been snoring every
night this week, Cleveland.

02:32.136 --> 02:34.402
Why don't you just go in there
and wake him up?

02:34.404 --> 02:36.972
I would, but he started
locking his door at night

02:36.974 --> 02:39.407
because he's scared
of the rock band KISS.

02:39.409 --> 02:42.477
He saw them on <i>American Idol</i>
and thinks they're real.

02:42.479 --> 02:45.180
Cleveland, he is 14 years old.
I know.

02:45.182 --> 02:47.766
Well, I read
in <i>Reactionary Parent Magazine</i>

02:47.768 --> 02:49.835
that sometimes snoring
is a symptom

02:49.837 --> 02:51.503
of serious health problems.

02:51.505 --> 02:52.771
Snoring is?

02:52.773 --> 02:55.240
RALLO:
Stop making so much noise,
you fat loser.

02:55.242 --> 02:57.075
He can't help it, Rallo.

02:57.077 --> 02:58.577
RALLO:
I wasn't talking to him.

02:58.579 --> 03:01.112
Oh, I'm sorry, good night.

03:01.114 --> 03:05.250
I make so much noise sometimes.
Stupid.

03:05.252 --> 03:07.369
[♪]

03:08.504 --> 03:10.539
Here, put these Band-Aids
in your pocket.

03:10.541 --> 03:14.209
But, Daddy, that's stealing.
They're free. Hurry.

03:14.211 --> 03:16.945
Junior, your tests are back
and it appears you have

03:16.947 --> 03:20.082
one of the most overdiagnosed
childhood disorders in America,

03:20.084 --> 03:21.383
sleep apnea.

03:21.385 --> 03:23.952
But you really have it.
Probably.

03:23.954 --> 03:27.089
I think a light diet and losing
a few pounds should solve this.

03:27.091 --> 03:30.392
And what I imagine are countless
other problems in your life.

03:30.394 --> 03:34.196
Doctor, Junior's been
on a "light diet" for years.

03:34.198 --> 03:36.098
Yeah, what else you got?

03:36.100 --> 03:38.250
Well, there is something
called a CPAP machine.

03:38.252 --> 03:40.152
Here you go.
Cool. Heh-heh.

03:40.154 --> 03:43.055
I'm Jacques Cousteau. Ow.

03:43.057 --> 03:44.789
Hey, those aren't
your Band-Aids.

03:44.791 --> 03:48.394
Ah! Junior. Stealing?

03:48.396 --> 03:51.730
[♪]

03:51.732 --> 03:54.432
Good morning, family.
Oh, sweet Lord.

03:54.434 --> 03:56.835
How'd you sleep, Junior?
Better than ever.

03:56.837 --> 03:59.104
I'm alert,
I have tons of energy,

03:59.106 --> 04:01.340
and my poo came out
with no tears.

04:01.342 --> 04:04.743
I feel so good, I'm gonna wear
this mask to school today.

04:04.745 --> 04:07.079
Junior, I don't want you
to embarrass yourself

04:07.081 --> 04:08.479
by wearing that to school.

04:08.481 --> 04:11.349
But if you're going to,
at least take off your underwear

04:11.351 --> 04:13.451
so no one can pull it
over your head.

04:13.453 --> 04:15.520
Okay.

04:16.655 --> 04:19.524
One problem at a time,
Donna.

04:19.526 --> 04:21.260
[♪]

04:27.350 --> 04:29.167
[PANTING]

04:56.896 --> 05:00.031
["POPEYE" THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

05:14.346 --> 05:15.830
[ALL LAUGH]

05:15.832 --> 05:17.699
Look, everybody,
it's Robohog.

05:17.701 --> 05:19.767
Hey,
it's Optimus Prime Rib.

05:19.769 --> 05:21.503
[ALL LAUGH]

05:21.505 --> 05:24.606
Get it? Because in that mask,
you look like a fat robot.

05:24.608 --> 05:26.074
[ALL LAUGH]

05:26.076 --> 05:27.225
No, I got it.

05:27.227 --> 05:30.028
But I need my mask
to breathe properly.

05:30.030 --> 05:31.095
Breathe properly?

05:31.097 --> 05:33.097
What are you,
gay for oxygen?

05:33.099 --> 05:34.866
Derek,
we all need oxygen.

05:34.868 --> 05:36.501
Yeah, man.
Stick to the fat jokes.

05:36.503 --> 05:37.636
Fine.

05:37.638 --> 05:39.604
What's up, fatty?
[ALL LAUGH]

05:39.606 --> 05:41.339
He's back.

05:47.062 --> 05:49.331
Why so blue, Junior?

05:49.333 --> 05:52.166
I got made fun of
because of my fat problem.

05:52.168 --> 05:54.469
I'm sorry to hear that.

05:55.638 --> 05:57.422
[WHIMPERING]

05:58.858 --> 06:00.258
You want a piece of pizza?

06:00.260 --> 06:04.546
Oh, sure. Thank you.

06:04.548 --> 06:07.832
You know,
it seems like us heavy-sets

06:07.834 --> 06:12.371
are the only group you're
allowed to make fun of anymore.

06:12.373 --> 06:16.308
Well, us and even
the smartest of the Polish.

06:16.310 --> 06:19.311
There should be a hate crime law
for people like us.

06:19.313 --> 06:22.597
Or a weight crime law.

06:22.599 --> 06:25.099
That's it.
If we got a law passed

06:25.101 --> 06:26.601
to protect us from ridicule

06:26.603 --> 06:28.437
all our problems
would be solved.

06:28.439 --> 06:29.771
Then it's settled.

06:29.773 --> 06:32.607
We're doing it.
Thanks, Miss Kendra.

06:32.609 --> 06:35.677
Now, give me a hug.

06:35.679 --> 06:37.646
[GROANING]

06:41.568 --> 06:44.369
Cleveland, we are completely
out of graham crackers.

06:44.371 --> 06:47.072
Will you keep an eye on Rallo
while I run to the store?

06:47.074 --> 06:49.941
Make sure he stays
out of the pool.

06:49.943 --> 06:52.761
Cleveland.
Cleveland, do you hear me?

06:52.763 --> 06:56.364
Yes, Donna.
Lou Ferrigno could hear you.

06:56.366 --> 06:58.650
[♪]

06:58.652 --> 07:03.155
He drops back. Oh, he sees
an opening and he takes-- Oh!

07:03.157 --> 07:06.624
Help, I can't swim!

07:06.626 --> 07:09.294
Somebody help me!

07:11.064 --> 07:13.031
[♪]

07:13.033 --> 07:14.933
CLEVELAND:
Oh, my God, no!

07:14.935 --> 07:18.270
They're doing another season
of <i>The Bachelor?</i>

07:18.272 --> 07:21.672
Mm. This world.

07:27.213 --> 07:29.147
[♪]

07:32.552 --> 07:35.454
Wait a minute, I don't remember
buying a coaster

07:35.456 --> 07:38.056
shaped like a dead kid!

07:38.058 --> 07:39.991
Rallo, my angel.

07:39.993 --> 07:41.660
Oh, can you hear me?

07:41.662 --> 07:46.531
Oh, God, if you die,
I am never getting laid again.

07:50.436 --> 07:51.502
[GRUNTS]

08:01.747 --> 08:06.184
Ugh. I should have done this
before the plunger.

08:06.186 --> 08:08.720
I gotta bury the body.

08:11.057 --> 08:12.423
[COUGHING]

08:12.425 --> 08:14.593
Even better.

08:14.595 --> 08:17.395
Rallo, are you okay?

08:17.397 --> 08:19.715
You saved my life, old man.

08:19.717 --> 08:23.652
From now on, you need anything,
you come to me.

08:23.654 --> 08:25.320
Oh, I don't need anything
from you.

08:25.322 --> 08:28.689
Other than to never mention this
to your mother.

08:28.691 --> 08:30.492
Why not? You're a hero.

08:30.494 --> 08:32.593
Yes, but, Rallo,

08:32.595 --> 08:36.164
if your mother finds out you
were running around this pool,

08:36.166 --> 08:39.501
ooh-hoo, boy,
will she be mad at you.

08:39.503 --> 08:42.703
She might even ban you
from the pool completely.

08:42.705 --> 08:44.772
A hero and a genius.

08:44.774 --> 08:46.141
I won't say a word.

08:46.143 --> 08:48.276
But I will never forget this,

08:48.278 --> 08:50.311
like E.T. never forgot Elliott.

08:50.313 --> 08:51.530
[RINGS]

08:51.532 --> 08:55.467
Hello?
E.T.: <i>E.T. phone Elliott?</i>

08:55.469 --> 08:56.635
Oh, hey.

08:56.637 --> 08:57.669
<i>What's up?</i>

08:57.671 --> 08:59.571
Nothing since we talked
yesterday.

08:59.573 --> 09:01.973
<i>Do you still have that bike?</i>

09:01.975 --> 09:03.375
Again, no, E.T.

09:03.377 --> 09:05.977
I don't still have the bike
I had when I was 10.

09:05.979 --> 09:08.279
<i>What about the blanket?</i>

09:08.281 --> 09:10.081
Nope, no blanket either.

09:10.083 --> 09:12.250
Listen, I gotta go, E.T.

09:12.252 --> 09:15.119
<i>Elliott!</i>

09:15.121 --> 09:17.288
What?
<i>Hi.</i>

09:17.290 --> 09:19.991
[ALL CHATTERING]

09:19.993 --> 09:24.295
My name is Cleveland Brown Jr.,
and I'm here to recruit you.

09:24.297 --> 09:26.982
For too long,
this world has marginalized

09:26.984 --> 09:28.483
and ridiculed fat people,

09:28.485 --> 09:31.269
assuming that just because
our feet are often numb

09:31.271 --> 09:32.738
that we don't have feelings.

09:32.740 --> 09:35.307
But they're wrong!

09:35.309 --> 09:37.842
My name is Kendra Krinklesac.

09:37.844 --> 09:41.095
And our ballot measure
guarantees equality

09:41.097 --> 09:44.198
for all obese heterosexuals.

09:44.200 --> 09:45.784
[SOBBING]

09:45.786 --> 09:48.219
Hey, it'll be okay.

09:48.221 --> 09:51.556
We'll vote for this one
and then in time...

09:51.558 --> 09:53.591
In time.

09:57.063 --> 09:59.498
Glad I lived to do this for you,
old man.

09:59.500 --> 10:02.934
Because I saved you.
I saved you. Mm-hm.

10:02.936 --> 10:05.137
Yes, I did. Yes, I did.

10:05.139 --> 10:07.372
Cleveland, how many times
do I have to tell you

10:07.374 --> 10:10.575
not to leave your baseball cards
spread out all over our bed?

10:10.577 --> 10:13.578
I was seeing which guys I had
and which guys I need.

10:13.580 --> 10:15.647
Cleveland, how many times do--?
Hold up.

10:15.649 --> 10:18.517
You need to treat this man
with the respect he deserves.

10:18.519 --> 10:19.784
Uh, uh...
Excuse me?

10:19.786 --> 10:21.753
No, Cleveland,
she needs to hear.

10:21.755 --> 10:23.455
This man's a hero. He saved--

10:23.457 --> 10:27.358
Money on car insurance
with GEICO. Ha-ha-ha. Get it?

10:27.360 --> 10:29.443
What the hell
are you talking about?

10:29.445 --> 10:32.881
Hey, I almost forgot, Djimon
Hounsou's in the front yard.

10:32.883 --> 10:34.515
Really?

10:34.517 --> 10:36.718
[SIGHS]

10:38.554 --> 10:40.855
You were supposed to be
watching me the other day

10:40.857 --> 10:42.691
when I fell in the pool,
weren't you?

10:42.693 --> 10:44.959
Yes, I was. Yes, I was.

10:44.961 --> 10:47.528
And I almost drowned?
Mm-hm.

10:47.530 --> 10:49.898
You realize I own you now,
right?

10:49.900 --> 10:51.599
That you do, yes.

10:51.601 --> 10:53.902
Empty your pockets
so I can take what I want.

10:53.904 --> 10:55.603
Dang.

11:04.112 --> 11:07.198
Well, well, well,
what have we here?

11:07.200 --> 11:09.667
That's my grandfather's
pocket watch.

11:09.669 --> 11:12.070
I think you mean
my pocket watch.

11:12.072 --> 11:14.572
There is no way
on God's Earth

11:14.574 --> 11:16.908
I am letting you
have that watch.

11:16.910 --> 11:19.794
Aah! Cleveland wasn't
watching me and I almost drowned

11:19.796 --> 11:22.730
in his white-trash-above-ground
pool.

11:22.732 --> 11:25.150
Here, take the watch,
you little hombitch.

11:25.152 --> 11:27.418
All right.
I love this watch.

11:27.420 --> 11:28.703
It's classy.

11:28.705 --> 11:30.838
[IN ENGLISH ACCENT]
What time is it, you say?

11:30.840 --> 11:33.674
A quarter past the hour.

11:33.676 --> 11:35.810
[♪]

11:35.812 --> 11:37.545
So, Cleveland and Lester,

11:37.547 --> 11:39.681
how does it feel
to have your son and wife

11:39.683 --> 11:41.449
be the laughingstock
of our town?

11:41.451 --> 11:42.684
Shut up, Eraserhead.

11:42.686 --> 11:45.053
Laughingstock?
What are you talking about?

11:45.055 --> 11:47.288
According to the news,
Junior and Kendra

11:47.290 --> 11:49.824
are the king and queen
of the fatties.

11:49.826 --> 11:52.627
[ALL LAUGHING]

11:52.629 --> 11:54.896
I boned a fat chick once
as a goof.

11:54.898 --> 11:57.866
Had to date her for eight months
before she let me. Fell in love.

11:57.868 --> 11:59.934
Asked her to marry me.
She said no.

11:59.936 --> 12:01.870
Said she boned a short guy
as a goof.

12:01.872 --> 12:03.604
Pfft.
Chicks aren't funny.

12:03.606 --> 12:05.190
Uh, drink up,
fellas.

12:05.192 --> 12:07.692
You don't wanna be sober
when you walk into that booth

12:07.694 --> 12:09.361
and see
your names associated

12:09.363 --> 12:11.262
with the grossest thing
on Earth.

12:11.264 --> 12:12.998
Fat people.
Prolapsed rectums.

12:13.000 --> 12:17.502
Hey! Prolapsed rectums
are not funny!

12:19.989 --> 12:22.707
[♪]

12:24.426 --> 12:26.845
Shh, shh. It's coming.
It's results time.

12:26.847 --> 12:29.748
I wish I could cross my fingers.

12:29.750 --> 12:31.949
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Here now with the news,</i>
<i>Dwayne Meighan.</i>

12:31.951 --> 12:34.885
<i>Good evening.</i>
<i>I'm Dwayne Meighan.</i>

12:34.887 --> 12:38.055
<i>Today was the day</i>
<i>when they had an election.</i>

12:38.057 --> 12:40.458
<i>Everybody went</i>
<i>and said what they had</i>

12:40.460 --> 12:43.127
<i>about a measure</i>
<i>called the Brown-Krinklesac</i>

12:43.129 --> 12:46.331
<i>for the fat people</i>
<i>or the fat individual.</i>

12:46.333 --> 12:49.867
<i>They had people that you were</i>
<i>signed your name on a sheet</i>

12:49.869 --> 12:54.405
<i>and then you could say</i>
<i>yes or no and that was for you</i>

12:54.407 --> 12:58.909
<i>but everybody got to say</i>
<i>yes or no.</i>

12:58.911 --> 13:02.647
<i>At this juncture, several</i>
<i>people on a voluntary basis</i>

13:02.649 --> 13:05.583
<i>had counted</i>
<i>what they had called a ballot</i>

13:05.585 --> 13:08.185
<i>that was what they had said</i>
<i>yes or no.</i>

13:08.187 --> 13:10.187
<i>They had made one pile for yes</i>

13:10.189 --> 13:12.823
<i>and another pile</i>
<i>for those who said no.</i>

13:12.825 --> 13:15.560
<i>Both piles where then counted,</i>
<i>double-checked</i>

13:15.562 --> 13:18.529
<i>as the result</i>
<i>of which was made official.</i>

13:18.531 --> 13:23.100
<i>Word had been the measure</i>
<i>had actually been defeated.</i>

13:23.102 --> 13:24.486
[BOTH SIGH]

13:24.488 --> 13:26.321
I'm sorry, Junior.

13:26.323 --> 13:27.722
<i>They had a camera out</i>

13:27.724 --> 13:30.325
<i>at what they had called</i>
<i>a polling place earlier</i>

13:30.327 --> 13:31.792
<i>with my friend Larvell.</i>

13:31.794 --> 13:33.161
<i>Larvell?</i>

13:33.163 --> 13:35.463
<i>Um, I'm actually</i>
<i>at the polling place</i>

13:35.465 --> 13:37.832
<i>and, um,</i>
<i>there were so many had--</i>

13:37.834 --> 13:40.701
<i>Some guys--</i>
<i>Hey, wait, here are some guys--</i>

13:40.703 --> 13:44.972
<i>Hey, guys, did y'all vote</i>
<i>on Brown-Krinklesac?</i>

13:44.974 --> 13:47.641
<i>Yeah.</i>
<i>These guys voted.</i>

13:47.643 --> 13:49.543
<i>Hey, how did y'all vote?</i>

13:49.545 --> 13:51.879
<i>We both voted,</i>
<i>"Hell, no."</i>

13:51.881 --> 13:55.016
<i>That's right. N-O. No.</i>

13:55.018 --> 13:57.484
<i>So suck on that, fatties.</i>

13:57.486 --> 14:00.554
[BOTH LAUGHING]

14:01.824 --> 14:04.526
I think we're in big trouble,
Lester.

14:04.528 --> 14:08.262
That is until
we disappear.

14:08.264 --> 14:10.231
[SCREAMING]

14:12.001 --> 14:16.738
Seems like that's the story now.
Hmm.

14:20.058 --> 14:21.526
You know, Miss Kendra,

14:21.528 --> 14:25.096
right now, I weigh more than
I ever have in my whole life.

14:25.098 --> 14:29.501
And yet I've never felt smaller.
That's beautiful.

14:29.503 --> 14:32.003
You know what's ironical,
Junior?

14:32.005 --> 14:34.505
Nothing.
Ironical isn't a word.

14:34.507 --> 14:37.342
Nothing is ironical,
but go ahead.

14:37.344 --> 14:41.462
I was just gonna say that
all I wanted was to be accepted,

14:41.464 --> 14:45.033
but now I feel more left out
than ever.

14:45.035 --> 14:46.618
That's beautiful too.

14:46.620 --> 14:49.754
Even though it's kind of exactly
what I just said.

14:49.756 --> 14:52.040
And it wasn't
just our families.

14:52.042 --> 14:56.945
This whole town
is full of skinny jerks.

14:56.947 --> 14:59.230
You know what?
We don't need them.

14:59.232 --> 15:01.566
There's got to be some place
better than this.

15:01.568 --> 15:04.134
Where people are free
to be who they are.

15:04.136 --> 15:07.422
Where a person is judged
not by the size of their belly

15:07.424 --> 15:09.924
but by the color of their skin.

15:09.926 --> 15:12.243
Huh?
Screw Stoolbend.

15:12.245 --> 15:14.679
We're hitting the road,
Junior.

15:14.681 --> 15:15.914
Yay!

15:15.916 --> 15:17.782
[STEPPENWOLF'S "BORN TO BE WILD"
PLAYING]

15:19.368 --> 15:22.737
<i>♪ Get your motor runnin' ♪</i>

15:22.739 --> 15:24.973
<i>♪ Head out on the highway</i>

15:27.776 --> 15:30.528
<i>♪ Lookin' for adventure ♪</i>

15:30.530 --> 15:32.997
<i>♪ In whatever comes our way</i>

15:36.351 --> 15:39.387
<i>♪ Yeah, darling</i>
<i>Go and make it happen ♪</i>

15:39.389 --> 15:40.688
<i>♪ Take the world in--</i>

15:46.962 --> 15:50.431
<i>♪ Born to be wild</i>

15:50.433 --> 15:53.334
What are you doing, man?
Where's my Kool-Aid?

15:53.336 --> 15:57.305
Rallo, I've been busting my butt
following your orders all day.

15:57.307 --> 15:59.340
I just finished
ironing your clothes

15:59.342 --> 16:02.143
and painting that Eazy-E mural
over your bed.

16:04.947 --> 16:07.148
I'm exhausted.
Give me a minute.

16:07.150 --> 16:09.717
A minute? Oh, is that how long
I was unconscious

16:09.719 --> 16:10.952
or was it longer?

16:10.954 --> 16:13.988
Now, get out of that pool
and make me a Kool-Aid.

16:15.691 --> 16:17.258
You're crazy!

16:17.260 --> 16:19.160
No,
I'm just bigger than you.

16:19.162 --> 16:21.863
You're 5 years old
and I'm not gonna let you

16:21.865 --> 16:24.365
order me around my own house
anymore.

16:24.367 --> 16:26.034
But you almost killed me!

16:26.036 --> 16:28.169
No, you almost killed you.

16:28.171 --> 16:30.038
I just wasn't
paying attention.

16:30.040 --> 16:31.339
And I should've been.

16:31.341 --> 16:34.175
I'm truly sorry.

16:34.177 --> 16:35.877
Aah! What was that for?

16:35.879 --> 16:38.346
That was for making me
eat a stick.

16:38.348 --> 16:41.015
We straight?
Y-Y-Yeah, w-we straight.

16:41.017 --> 16:43.684
Good.
I love you, Rallo.

16:43.686 --> 16:46.754
Now, learn to swim.
The river's that way.

16:46.756 --> 16:49.090
Yes, sir.

16:49.092 --> 16:52.360
Man, I got this
parenting thing down.

16:52.362 --> 16:55.763
Hm. Haven't seen Junior
in a couple days.

16:55.765 --> 16:57.631
[♪]

16:59.935 --> 17:02.437
You had me kick in
for gas money,

17:02.439 --> 17:05.039
but I notice
this runs on electricity.

17:05.041 --> 17:06.007
Hmm?

17:06.009 --> 17:09.243
[BABBLING]

17:09.245 --> 17:14.882
Junior, I think I see something
just over this hill.

17:14.884 --> 17:19.220
I've heard tell,
but I never knew it was real.

17:19.222 --> 17:23.140
They call it Wisconsin.

17:23.142 --> 17:25.109
[♪]

17:40.358 --> 17:42.443
[LAUGHING]

17:45.681 --> 17:47.649
[ALL CLAMORING]

17:58.127 --> 17:59.660
[MOOS]

18:07.069 --> 18:12.140
Look at me. I'm walking again.

18:13.592 --> 18:15.527
[GRUNTS]

18:15.529 --> 18:17.896
Hey, you folks,
wanna try some crazy butter?

18:17.898 --> 18:19.697
What's that?

18:19.699 --> 18:21.515
It's three sticks of butter
in a mug

18:21.517 --> 18:23.217
with melted cheese on top.

18:23.219 --> 18:25.369
Hells, yeah,
I want that crazy butter.

18:28.206 --> 18:30.408
[QUEEN'S "FAT BOTTOMED GIRLS"
PLAYING]

18:30.410 --> 18:35.613
<i>♪ Oh, won't you take me</i>
<i>Home tonight? ♪</i>

18:35.615 --> 18:39.617
<i>♪ Oh, down beside</i>
<i>Your red firelight ♪</i>

18:39.619 --> 18:41.753
[GULPING]

18:41.755 --> 18:45.539
<i>♪ Oh, and you give it</i>
<i>All you got ♪</i>

18:45.541 --> 18:47.258
<i>♪ Fat bottomed girls</i>

18:47.260 --> 18:49.660
<i>♪ You make the rockin' world</i>
<i>Go round ♪</i>

18:55.200 --> 18:58.052
<i>♪ Hey, listen here</i>

18:58.054 --> 18:59.654
<i>♪ Fat bottomed girls</i>

18:59.656 --> 19:03.758
<i>♪ You make the rockin' world</i>
<i>Go round ♪</i>

19:05.961 --> 19:07.946
[♪]

19:12.751 --> 19:14.719
[VOICES CHATTERING]

19:26.898 --> 19:28.566
[BOTH PANTING]

19:28.568 --> 19:31.302
I thought eating
anything and everything

19:31.304 --> 19:33.771
would solve all my problems,

19:33.773 --> 19:36.374
but maybe the eating

19:36.376 --> 19:40.078
is a symptom
of other problems.

19:40.080 --> 19:43.747
You just blew my mind.

19:43.749 --> 19:46.600
Out of my way, large sir.
Move it.

19:46.602 --> 19:48.736
Oh, everybody's sticky.

19:48.738 --> 19:50.388
Dad.
Lester?

19:50.390 --> 19:52.790
How did you find us?

19:52.792 --> 19:55.226
I got a LoJack for your Rascal
when Cleve--

19:55.228 --> 19:57.829
Uh, those Puerto Ricans moved in
down the street.

19:57.831 --> 20:01.565
Well, you wasted your time
coming here.

20:01.567 --> 20:03.567
You hurt me, Lester.

20:03.569 --> 20:06.170
Kendra,
you may be morbidly obese,

20:06.172 --> 20:09.473
but I'm the one
who acted like a big fat fool.

20:09.475 --> 20:12.927
Because, disgust me or not,
I love you.

20:12.929 --> 20:15.363
Please come back.
I don't know.

20:15.365 --> 20:18.966
I strongly urge you
to consider your options.

20:18.968 --> 20:22.236
Let's go home.

20:25.340 --> 20:27.725
Let's go home too, Junior.

20:27.727 --> 20:30.160
Not until you apologize
for what you did.

20:30.162 --> 20:31.862
I'm sorry you're fat.

20:31.864 --> 20:34.465
Junior, fat people
don't deserve special treatment

20:34.467 --> 20:36.099
just because they're fat.

20:36.101 --> 20:38.135
Being fat is a choice.

20:38.137 --> 20:39.871
Do you choose to be pudgy?

20:39.873 --> 20:41.339
Wha...?

20:41.341 --> 20:43.874
Y-You think I'm pudgy?

20:43.876 --> 20:46.544
Hurtful.

20:46.546 --> 20:48.979
That's it. No more fries.

20:48.981 --> 20:52.115
Just chips. Or cheese fries.

20:52.117 --> 20:55.753
You want some cheese fries?
I could eat.

20:55.755 --> 20:58.506
<i>♪ Hey</i>

20:58.508 --> 21:01.175
<i>♪ I was just a skinny lad</i>

21:01.177 --> 21:03.711
<i>♪ Never knew no good from bad</i>

21:05.780 --> 21:07.748
[♪]

21:38.814 --> 21:41.949
[English - US - Line 21]
